<div class="box-body">

  <div style="float:right;">Date - <%= Time.zone.now.to_date %> </div><br><br>

   <b><center>Joining Letter</center></b><br><br>

  <p> Dear Mr./Miss.<b> <%= @employee.first_name %> <%= @employee.middle_name %> <%= @employee.last_name %> </b> </p>
  <p> Welcome to <b> <%= current_user.employee.company_location.company.description %> </b></p>
  <p> I am pleased to offer you employment in the position of  <b> <%= @employee.joining_detail.employee_designation.try(:name) %> with <%= current_user.employee.company_location.company.description %> </b></p>

  <p> I am eager to have you as part of our team. I foresee your potential skills as a valuable contribution to our company and clients. Your appointment as <%= @employee.joining_detail.employee_designation.try(:name) %> will commence on date --------------- . </p>

  <p> As <%= @employee.joining_detail.employee_designation.try(:name) %> , you will be entitled to a monthly starting remuneration of Rs 00,000/- (Rupees…………. only) which indicates cost to company. You will be on a probation period of six months. Regular performance review will be conducted to assess your performance and suitability. Your continued employment at <b><%= current_user.employee.company_location.company.description %></b> is dependent on your successful completion of the probationary period. Your salary will be reviewed after a period of 6 months and thereafter every 12 months. You will be entitled to all allowances ad benefits whatsoever decided by the management.You shall receive your payment before 5th of every month.
  Your signing this appointment letter confirms your acceptance of the terms and conditions and that you would be joining <b><%= current_user.employee.company_location.company.description %></b> on the given date.

  <p>I am looking forward to working with you. </p>
  <P>HR</P>
  <p>For <b> <%= current_user.employee.company_location.company.description %> </b></p>
</div>
